The '''2011 AFF U-23 Youth Championship''' was going to be the second edition of the tournament which was set to take place between the 16 and 26 July 2011 in [[Palembang]], [[Indonesia]] but was postponed on 7 July because the [[Gelora Sriwijaya Stadium]] was under renovation and would be moved to Jakarta.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.aseanfootball.org/?p=5381 |title=PRE-SEA GAMES CHAMPIONSHIP IN PALEMBANG POSTPONED |work=AseanFootball.org |publisher=ASEAN Football Federation |date=2011-07-06 |accessdate=2011-07-06 }}</ref> It was considered by the [[ASEAN Football Federation]] as the preparatory tournament for the [[Football at the 2011 Southeast Asian Games|2011 Southeast Asian Games]], which would also be held in [[Indonesia]].<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.aseanfootball.org/?p=4186 |title=Laos and Indonesia hold two AFF tournaments each in 2011 |work=AseanFootball.org |publisher=ASEAN Football Federation |date=2011-02-19 |accessdate=2011-05-12 }}</ref> The 2011 competition was later cancelled.
