==Events== *[[202 BC]] &ndash; [[Emperor Gaozu of Han|Liu Bang]] is enthroned as the [[Emperor of China]], beginning four centuries of rule by the [[Han dynasty]]. * [[628]] &ndash; [[Khosrow II]] is executed by [[Mihr Hormozd]] under the orders of [[Kavadh II]]. * [[870]] &ndash; The [[Fourth Council of Constantinople (Roman Catholic)|Fourth Council of Constantinople]] closes. *[[1246]] &ndash; The [[Siege of Jaén (1245–46)|siege of Jaén]] ends in the context of the Spanish [[Reconquista]] resulting in the Castilian takeover of the city from the Taifa of Jaen. *[[1525]] &ndash; [[Aztec]] king [[Cuauhtémoc]] is executed on the order of conquistador [[Hernán Cortés]]. *[[1638]] &ndash; The Scottish [[National Covenant]] is signed in [[Edinburgh]]. *[[1700]] &ndash; Today is followed by [[March 1]] in Sweden, thus creating the [[Swedish calendar]]. *[[1710]] &ndash; [[Battle of Helsingborg]]: 14,000 Danish invaders under [[Jørgen Rantzau]] are decisively defeated by an equally sized Swedish force under [[Magnus Stenbock]]. This is the last time Swedish and Danish troops meet on Swedish soil. *[[1728]] &ndash; [[Baji Rao I|Peshwa Bajirao I]] of the [[Maratha Empire]] defeats [[Mir Qamar-ud-din Khan|Asaf Jah I]] in the [[Battle of Palkhed]] *[[1784]] &ndash; [[John Wesley]] charters the [[Methodism|Methodist Church]]. *[[1827]] &ndash; The [[Baltimore and Ohio Railroad]] is incorporated, becoming the first railroad in America offering commercial transportation of both people and freight. *[[1838]] &ndash; [[Robert Nelson (insurrectionist)|Robert Nelson]], leader of the [[Patriotes]], proclaims the independence of [[Lower Canada]] (today [[Quebec]]). *[[1844]] &ndash; A gun on {{USS|Princeton|1843|6}} explodes while the boat is on a [[Potomac River]] cruise, killing six people, including two [[United States Cabinet]] members. *[[1847]] &ndash; The [[Battle of the Sacramento River]] during the [[Mexican–American War]] is a decisive victory for the United States leading to the capture of [[Chihuahua City|Chihuahua]]. *[[1849]] &ndash; Regular [[steamship]] service from the east to the west coast of the United States begins with the arrival of the {{SS|California|1848|6}} in [[San Francisco Bay]], four months 22 days after leaving [[New York Harbor]]. *[[1867]] &ndash; Seventy years of [[Holy See–United States relations]] are ended by a [[United States Congress|Congressional]] ban on federal funding of [[diplomacy|diplomatic]] [[Diplomatic rank#Multilateral diplomacy|envoys]] to the Vatican and are not restored until January 10, 1984. *[[1870]] &ndash; The [[Bulgarian Exarchate]] is established by decree of Sultan [[Abdülaziz of the Ottoman Empire]]. *[[1874]] &ndash; One of the longest cases ever heard in an English court ends when the defendant is convicted of [[perjury]] for [[Tichborne case|attempting to assume the identity]] of the heir to the [[Tichborne baronets|Tichborne baronetcy]]. *[[1893]] &ndash; The {{USS|Indiana|BB-1|6}}, the lead ship of [[Indiana-class battleship|her class]] and the first [[battleship]] in the [[United States Navy]] comparable to foreign battleships of the time, is launched. *[[1897]] &ndash; Queen [[Ranavalona III]], the last monarch of [[Madagascar]], is deposed by a French military force. *[[1900]] &ndash; The [[Second Boer War]]: The 118-day "[[Siege of Ladysmith]]" is lifted. *[[1904]] &ndash; [[S.L. Benfica]] is founded in [[Portugal]]. *[[1922]] &ndash; The United Kingdom ends its [[protectorate]] over [[Egypt]] through a [[Unilateral Declaration of Egyptian Independence|Unilateral Declaration of Independence]]. *[[1925]] &ndash; The [[1925 Charlevoix–Kamouraska earthquake|Charlevoix-Kamouraska earthquake]] strikes northeastern North America. *[[1933]] &ndash; ''[[Gleichschaltung]]'': The [[Reichstag Fire Decree]] is passed in Germany a day after the [[Reichstag fire]]. *[[1935]] &ndash; [[DuPont]] scientist [[Wallace Carothers]] invents [[nylon]]. *[[1939]] &ndash; The erroneous word "[[dord]]" is discovered in the ''[[Webster's Dictionary|Webster's New International Dictionary, Second Edition]]'', prompting an investigation. *[[1940]] &ndash; [[Basketball]] is [[Broadcasting of sports events|televised]] for the first time ([[Fordham Rams|Fordham University]] vs. the [[Pittsburgh Panthers men's basketball|University of Pittsburgh]] in [[Madison Square Garden]]). *[[1942]] &ndash; The heavy cruiser {{USS|Houston|CA-30|6}} is sunk in the [[Battle of Sunda Strait]] with 693 crew members killed, along with {{HMAS|Perth|D29|6}} which lost 375 men. *[[1947]] &ndash; [[February 28 Incident]]: In [[Taiwan]], civil disorder is put down with the loss of an estimated 30,000 civilians. *[[1948]] &ndash; [[The Big Six (Ghana)|Christiansborg Cross-Roads shooting]] in the [[Gold Coast (British colony)|Gold Coast]], when a British police officer opens fire on a march of ex-servicemen, killing three of them and sparking [[1948 Accra Riots|major riots and looting in Accra]]. *[[1953]] &ndash; [[James Watson]] and [[Francis Crick]] announce to friends that they have determined the chemical structure of [[DNA]]; the formal announcement takes place on [[April 25]] following publication in April's ''[[Nature (journal)|Nature]]'' (pub. [[April 2]]). *[[1954]] &ndash; The first [[color television]] sets using the [[NTSC]] standard are offered for sale to the general public. *[[1958]] &ndash; A school bus in [[Floyd County, Kentucky]] hits a wrecker truck and plunges down an embankment into the rain-swollen [[Levisa Fork]] river. The driver and 26 children die in what remains [[Prestonsburg, Kentucky bus disaster|one of the worst school bus accidents]] in U.S. history. *[[1959]] &ndash; ''[[Discoverer 1]]'', an American [[spy satellite]] that is the first object intended to achieve a [[polar orbit]], is launched but fails to achieve orbit. *[[1972]] &ndash; [[China–United States relations]]: The United States and China sign the [[Shanghai Communiqué]]. *[[1975]] &ndash; In London, an underground train [[Moorgate tube crash|fails to stop]] at Moorgate terminus station and crashes into the end of the tunnel, killing 43 people. *[[1980]] &ndash; [[Andalusia]] approves its [[Autonomous communities of Spain|statute of autonomy]] through a [[referendum]]. *[[1983]] &ndash; The [[Goodbye, Farewell and Amen|final episode]] of [[M*A*S*H (TV series)|M*A*S*H]] airs, with almost 106 million viewers. It still holds the record for the highest viewership of a season finale. *[[1985]] &ndash; The [[Provisional Irish Republican Army]] carries out a [[1985 Newry mortar attack|mortar attack]] on the [[Royal Ulster Constabulary]] police station at [[Newry]], killing nine officers in the highest loss of life for the RUC on a single day. *[[1986]] &ndash; [[Olof Palme]], 26th [[Prime Minister of Sweden]], is [[Assassination of Olof Palme|assassinated in Stockholm]]. *[[1991]] &ndash; The first [[Gulf War]] ends. *[[1993]] &ndash; The [[Bureau of Alcohol, Tobacco and Firearms]] agents [[Waco siege|raid]] the [[Branch Davidian]] church in [[Waco, Texas]] with a warrant to arrest the group's leader [[David Koresh]]. Four ATF agents and six Davidians die in the initial raid, starting a [[Waco siege|51-day standoff]]. *[[1995]] &ndash; Former Australian Liberal party leader [[John Hewson]] resigns from the Australian parliament almost two years after losing the [[Australian federal election, 1993]]. *[[1997]] &ndash; An [[1997 Ardabil earthquake|earthquake]] in northern [[Iran]] is responsible for about 3,000 deaths. * 1997 &ndash; [[GRB 970228]], a highly luminous flash of [[gamma ray]]s, strikes the Earth for 80 seconds, providing early evidence that [[gamma-ray burst]]s occur well beyond the [[Milky Way]]. *[[1998]] &ndash; First flight of [[RQ-4 Global Hawk]], the first [[unmanned aerial vehicle]] certified to file its own flight plans and fly regularly in U.S. civilian airspace. * 1998 &ndash; [[Kosovo War]]: [[Serbia and Montenegro|Serbian]] police begin the offensive against the [[Kosovo Liberation Army]] in [[Kosovo]]. *[[2002]] &ndash; During the [[2002 Gujarat riots|religious violence in Gujarat]], the 97 people killed in the [[Naroda Patiya massacre]] and 69 in [[Gulbarg Society massacre]]. *[[2004]] &ndash; Over one million [[Taiwan]]ese participate in the [[228 Hand-in-Hand rally]] form a {{convert|500|km|mi|adj=on}} long human chain to commemorate the [[February 28 Incident]] in [[1947]] *[[2005]] &ndash; A [[2005 Al Hillah bombing|suicide bombing]] at a police recruiting centre in [[Al Hillah]], [[Iraq]] kills 127. *[[2013]] &ndash; [[Pope Benedict XVI]] [[Resignation of Pope Benedict XVI|resigns]] as the pope of the [[Catholic Church]], becoming the first pope to do so since [[Pope Gregory XII]], in 1415.
