{{Infobox motorsport championship | name = SMP F4 Championship | logo = | image-size = | caption = | category = [[Fédération Internationale de l'Automobile|FIA]] [[Formula 4]] | region = Europe | inaugural = | inaugural2 = [[2015 SMP F4 Championship season|2015]] | folded = | classes = | drivers = | teams = | constructors = [[Tatuus]] | engines = [[Abarth]] | tyres = [[Hankook]] | champion driver = {{flagicon|FIN}} Konsta Lappalainen | champion team = | manufacturer = | constructor = | website = [http://smpf4championship.com/ Official website] | current_season = 2018 SMP F4 Championship }}
The '''SMP F4 Championship''' (also known as the '''F4 NEZ Championship by SMP Racing''') is a racing series regulated according to [[Fédération Internationale de l'Automobile|FIA]] [[Formula 4]] regulations. It is based in the FIA's North European Zone and the Netherlands, and is only open to drivers from these countries. The inaugural season will be the [[2015 SMP F4 Championship season|2015 SMP F4 Championship]].
==History== [[Gerhard Berger]] and the FIA Singleseater Commission launched the FIA Formula 4 in March 2013.<ref>{{cite web|title=FIA reveals Formula 4 plan|url=http://www.autosport.com/news/report.php/id/106219|work=[[Autosport]]|accessdate=11 December 2014}}</ref> The goal of the Formula 4 is to make the ladder to [[Formula One]] more transparent. Besides sporting and technical regulations, costs are regulated too. A car to compete in this category may not exceed €30.000 in purchase. A single season in Formula 4 may not exceed €100.000 in costs. The SMP F4 will be the one of the second phase Formula 4 championship to be launched. The first phase championships was the [[Italian F4 Championship]] and the [[Formula 4 Sudamericana]] which started in 2014. The SMP championship was launched by [[SMP Racing]], the Russian Automobile Federation, [[Koiranen GP]] and [[AKK-Motorsport]] on 22 July 2014.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.paddockscout.com/koiranen-launches-new-f4-series-for-north-europe/|title=Koiranen announces new F4 series for North Europe|last=Allen|first=Peter|date=22 July 2014|publisher=Paddock Scout|accessdate=11 December 2014}}</ref> Italian race car constructor [[Tatuus]] was contracted to design and build all the cars.
The championship expanded out of the FIA North European Zone for its second season. Following the failure to establish a separate Formula 4 championship in the Benelux region, it will incorporate two rounds in the Netherlands, and will award a Dutch Formula 4 Trophy for these two rounds plus a standalone Formula 4 Festival.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.paddockscout.com/dutch-f4-concept-to-form-part-of-smp-series-from-2016/32855|title=Dutch F4 concept to form part of SMP series from 2016|last=Allen|first=Peter|date=8 January 2016|publisher=Paddock Scout|accessdate=10 January 2016}}</ref> [[MP Motorsport]] will also operate cars alongside Koiranen GP, which ran all drivers in the inaugural season.
==Car== {{also|Tatuus F4-T014}} The championship features [[Tatuus]] designed and built cars. The cars will be constructed out of [[carbon fibre]] and feature a [[monocoque]] chassis. The engine is a 1.4 turbo [[Abarth]]. This is the same engine as in the [[Italian F4 Championship]].
